data.title: Wayland, Massachusetts Population 2024
data.text:
Poverty in Wayland

The race most likely to be in poverty in Wayland is Black , with 13.45% below the poverty level.

The race least likely to be in poverty in Wayland is Hispanic , with 1.33% below the poverty level.

The poverty rate among those that worked full-time for the past 12 months was 0.66% . Among those working part-time, it was 4.73% , and for those that did not work, the poverty rate was 8.76% .
